UP|45|cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|This was an interesting competitive hand. First lets discuss the bidding then we will discuss the play a bit. With my shortness in the majors, some people would choose to bid 3C with my hand, particularly since pard is a passed hand, and I would not quarrel with that. But I felt I had a pretty good hand, and also six not seven clubs, so I chose 2C rather than 3C. |
PG| ***** 20 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|What should Elizabeth do? I think negative double is best, rather than a 3C bid to show a limit raise in diamonds. 2H is an interesting call by Pam, since it shows her values and gets me off to the best lead. However, it normally would tend to show a fifth heart. Another possibility from Pam is 2D, limit raise in clubs. But 2H worked out very well. Often lead directing bids do. |
PG| ***** 21 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Marty Bergen would agree with Pam's bid. So, you are in good company Pam. The rest of the auction is fine. Elizabeth, with her void in clubs had a very good 4D bid. Voids are incredibly powerful when in the opponent's suit. Better than an Ace, because they guarantee no losers in that suit.|
PG| ***** 22 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As to the play, because of Pam's nice heart bid, we got off to the best lead. otherwise we don't get our ruffs. And Anna may even make the hand. However once we get off to a heart lead, she is down, having to lose 2 hearts a ruff and a spade. My only suggestion to Anna is at trick four on the King of clubs, she pitch a heart from dummy rather than a spade. |
PG| ***** 23 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Then she will not lose to the Jack of hearts, and may only be down one. One other minor point. Pam with her spade holding would like a spade back. So, at trick three when she leads a heart back, it should be the Jack, not the 10. It is not clear that is a suit preference, but the 10 is definitely a suit preference for clubs the lower suit. It doesn't really matter as Anna wins the Ace and can pitch a heart on the club anyway. |
PG| ***** 24 ***** |


