^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Let me address the 2 level overcall question. You do have to be careful with 2 level overcalls, particularly vulnerable. With a really good six card suit, which Pam has, it is not dangerous, as it is very difficult for the opponents to double. So, the better your suit, the fewer points you need. And the better your suit, the more you want to make a lead directing bid, so that is another reason to overcall. It is a risk/reward calculation, and with a good suit, the reward far outweighs the risk.|
