^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I am going to lead a spade, but let me discuss which one is the proper choice. Normally most people on BBO lead high from 3 small to deny an honor. However, when leading partner's suit that you have not supported, as in this case, it is better to lead count. You should lead low from three small in partner's suit if you have not supported her yet. That way he/she can tell how many you have, which is usually more important than whether or not you have an honor. |
