NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Before I go on, several people have asked me about Dee's 4 card major.  I personally think that if you have a preempt, you should preempt regardless of whether or not  you have a 4-card major. A preempt is a disruptive bid. You are giving up precision for aggressiveness. If you are worried about missing a better fit, then don't preempt. Usually, it is rare that you can make four of a major when you have a preempt. Therefore, I don't believe you need to worry about whether or not you have a 4-card major. I think preempting is one of the best bidding tools there is.|
