NT|^B@2
don211: Yes, but preempt tells your pard you do not have a 4-card major.|
PG| ***** 130 ***** |


cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Why should partner care if you have a 4-card major? By the way, many people disagree with me. I am just telling you how I feel. Certainly, if you are not comfortable preempting with a 4 card major, that is fine.|
PG| ***** 131 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Anyway, let's talk about balancing. Balancing means someone opens the bidding and it goes pass pass, so you are in the pass out seat. If you are in the pass out seat, and short in the opener's suit, you should strain to bid even with as little as 9 points at the 3 level! The point is, there are many hands that partner will have to pass over the preempt. So, the balancing position should strain to bid when short. |
